<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16138] CloudSolrStream silently returns empty stream when all nodes are down</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16138</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When reading from a `CloudSolrStream`, if all Solr cores are down, we receive an empty stream (EOF from the first `read()` operation).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, an exception should be thrown to represent that the Solr cluster is unreachable, even if the ZooKeeper cluster itself is reachable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
